WEBVTT

00:00.659 --> 00:02.836
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:02.836 --> 00:05.371
I WANT MY MONEY TOMORROW
OR I GO TO THE PRESS.

00:05.371 --> 00:07.473
SO YOU'RE SCREWING MY FATHER?

00:07.473 --> 00:09.510
Benny: AND YOU HAVEN'T PAID
THE MORTGAGE ON THIS HOUSE.

00:09.510 --> 00:10.977
IT'S ALMOST FIVE MONTHS BEHIND.

00:10.977 --> 00:13.346
WHY DO YOU ALWAYS HAVE TO
TOUCH ME WHEN YOU TALK TO ME?

00:13.346 --> 00:15.381
‐YOU EITHER GET CLEAN ‐‐
‐I AM CLEAN.

00:15.381 --> 00:16.950
WELL, THEN, STAY CLEAN!

00:16.950 --> 00:18.752
WELL, I CAN GO RUN AND GET
HIS PRESCRIPTION FOR HIM.

00:18.752 --> 00:19.953
PRESCRIPTION?

00:19.953 --> 00:21.822
YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN I'M IGNORED, DAD.

00:21.822 --> 00:24.224
AND SO HELP ME, IF YOU SO MUCH
AS MENTION A WORD OF THIS

00:24.224 --> 00:25.559
TO MY DAUGHTER,
YOU WILL REGRET IT

00:25.559 --> 00:28.529
FOR THE REST OF
YOUR VERY SHORT LIFE.

00:28.529 --> 00:31.598
♪♪♪♪

00:31.598 --> 00:34.735
I'M TELLING YOU, JIM, THERE'S
SOMETHING ABOUT THAT D. A.

00:34.735 --> 00:36.269
I DON'T TRUST.

00:36.269 --> 00:37.804
JUDGE CRYER.

00:37.804 --> 00:40.541
RUMOR HAS IT THAT YOU'RE RUNNING
FOR GOVERNOR. IS THAT TRUE?

00:42.008 --> 00:43.844
WELL, WITH THE PRESENT STATE
OF THE ECONOMY,

00:43.844 --> 00:45.612
I THINK SOMEONE
CERTAINLY SHOULD.

00:45.612 --> 00:47.080
DOES THAT MEAN YOU'LL RUN?

00:47.080 --> 00:48.615
THAT MEANS NO COMMENT, ROSE.

00:48.615 --> 00:49.916
OH, COME ON.

00:49.916 --> 00:51.985
GIVE ME SOMETHING, DAVID, JIM.

00:51.985 --> 00:53.787
ALL RIGHT, ROSE,
WHAT THAT MEANS IS THAT

00:53.787 --> 00:56.189
SINCE I HAVE RUN
MY OWN BUSINESS FOR 15 YEARS

00:56.189 --> 00:57.423
AND I'VE BEEN A JUDGE FOR 8

00:57.423 --> 00:59.192
THAT I KNOW SOMETHING
ABOUT BALANCING A BUDGET

00:59.192 --> 01:01.768
AND, ALSO,
THE EQUAL SCALES OF JUSTICE.

01:01.768 --> 01:03.003
SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE RUNNING.

01:03.003 --> 01:04.104
ROSE, GIVE HIM A BREAK.

01:04.104 --> 01:05.872
OH, YOU KNOW
I HAVE TO HAVE THE SCOOP.

01:05.872 --> 01:07.574
I'M THE OLDEST JOURNALIST
IN THIS TOWN,

01:07.574 --> 01:10.010
AND THESE YOUNG CROWS ARE
GIVING ME A RUN FOR THE MONEY,

01:10.010 --> 01:12.445
AND I NEED SOMETHING ‐‐
SOMETHING BIG.

01:12.445 --> 01:15.849
I PROMISE YOU, ONCE I DECIDE,
YOU'LL BE THE FIRST TO KNOW.

01:15.849 --> 01:17.383
OH, SHE'LL BE THE FIRST, HUH?

01:17.383 --> 01:18.885
THE FIRST.

01:18.885 --> 01:20.687
OKAY.

01:20.687 --> 01:22.589
OKAY.

01:24.490 --> 01:26.426
EXCUSE ME, GENTLEMEN.

01:26.426 --> 01:28.795
EXCUSE ME, MS. ROSE.
YOU'RE A REPORTER, RIGHT?

01:28.795 --> 01:30.396
WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE?

01:30.396 --> 01:32.733
I HAVE NO IDEA.

01:32.733 --> 01:34.467
WHY IS SHE TALKING TO ROSE?

01:34.467 --> 01:41.474
♪♪♪♪

01:41.474 --> 01:45.145
DO YOU THINK
SHE'S TELLING HER?

01:45.145 --> 01:46.813
NO.

01:46.813 --> 01:49.516
THEN WHY IS
SHE TALKING TO HER?

01:49.516 --> 01:51.918
LIKE I SAID, SHE'S SICK,
SHE'S TWISTED.

01:51.918 --> 01:53.754
I'M TELLING YOU,
SHE ENJOYS THIS.

01:53.754 --> 02:02.503
♪♪♪♪

02:02.503 --> 02:06.172
WHAT'S GOING ON
BETWEEN YOU TWO?

02:06.172 --> 02:07.140
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

02:07.140 --> 02:08.441
I MEAN JUST
WHAT THE HELL I SAID.

02:08.441 --> 02:10.644
NOTHING, NOTHING.

02:10.644 --> 02:17.617
♪♪♪♪

02:17.617 --> 02:24.558
♪♪♪♪

02:24.558 --> 02:27.260
I WILL HANDLE THIS.

02:27.260 --> 02:28.394
REALLY?

02:28.394 --> 02:30.063
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

02:30.063 --> 02:32.065
‐DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
‐DAVID ‐‐

02:32.065 --> 02:33.166
THIS GAL IS NOT GONNA

02:33.166 --> 02:34.935
BRING DOWN THIS CAMPAIGN
BEFORE IT EVEN STARTS.

02:34.935 --> 02:38.338
I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GOING TO DO.

02:38.338 --> 02:40.340
I'M GONNA HANDLE IT.

02:40.340 --> 02:44.410
THIS ENDS TODAY ‐‐

02:44.410 --> 02:46.046
TODAY, JIM.

02:46.046 --> 02:52.118
♪♪♪♪

02:52.118 --> 02:58.258
♪♪♪♪

03:06.573 --> 03:08.609
[ KNOCKING AT DOOR ]

03:08.609 --> 03:09.743
Benny: MAMA?

03:09.743 --> 03:13.279
[ KNOCKING CONTINUES ]

03:13.279 --> 03:14.414
MAMA?

03:14.414 --> 03:15.616
YEAH.

03:15.616 --> 03:17.918
WAKE UP.

03:17.918 --> 03:19.119
WHAT TIME IS IT?

03:19.119 --> 03:20.554
ALMOST 9:00.

03:20.554 --> 03:23.423
OH, LORD,
I'M LATE FOR WORK.

03:23.423 --> 03:25.091
YOU SHOULD HAVE WOKE ME UP,
BENNY.

03:25.091 --> 03:26.059
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

03:26.059 --> 03:27.861
YOUR BOSS CALLED ME.

03:27.861 --> 03:30.063
SHE SAID SINCE YOU WORKED
THAT PARTY SO LATE LAST NIGHT,

03:30.063 --> 03:32.365
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO IN.

03:32.365 --> 03:34.935
SHE WAS GONNA SLEEP IN,
SO SLEEP.

03:34.935 --> 03:37.771
OH, LORD GOD,
THANK YOU, JESUS.

03:37.771 --> 03:40.040
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:40.040 --> 03:42.809
OH, I NEEDED THAT REST.

03:42.809 --> 03:44.177
I KNOW YOU DID.

03:44.177 --> 03:48.114
THAT'S WHY I STARTED
NOT TO WAKE YOU UP AT ALL.

03:48.114 --> 03:50.250
NOW, YOU KNOW I'M GONNA HAVE
TO GO TO WORK SOMETIME.

03:50.250 --> 03:52.886
I KNOW, BUT YOU'RE TIRED.

03:52.886 --> 03:54.788
‐I'M FINE.
‐ARE YOU SURE?

03:54.788 --> 03:57.223
YEAH. THESE BILLS AIN'T GONNA
GET TIRED OF COMING.

03:57.223 --> 03:58.525
I CAN'T GET TIRED OF WORKING.

03:58.525 --> 04:00.193
MAMA, YOU FELL ASLEEP WITH
THESE BILLS ON THE BED

04:00.193 --> 04:01.401
AGAIN LAST NIGHT?

04:01.401 --> 04:04.204
I WAS TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHO TO PAY FIRST.

04:04.204 --> 04:07.040
I'M TELLING YOU, GETTING SICK
WITH NO MEDICAL INSURANCE

04:07.040 --> 04:09.876
WILL WIPE YOU OUT.

04:09.876 --> 04:12.713
I'M SO GRATEFUL TO GOD
THIS HOUSE IS PAID FOR.

04:12.713 --> 04:14.581
I MEAN IT. IF I HADN'T
PUT YOUR NAME ON IT

04:14.581 --> 04:16.883
BEFORE I WENT INTO THE HOSPITAL,
I'M SURE THEY WOULD HAVE BEEN

04:16.883 --> 04:18.118
COMING AFTER IT.

04:18.118 --> 04:20.086
MAMA, IT STILL AIN'T RIGHT
FOR YOU TO BE FALLING ASLEEP

04:20.086 --> 04:21.822
WITH ALL THIS ON YOUR MIND
EVERY NIGHT.

04:21.822 --> 04:25.626
BOY, YOU SEE WHAT'S NEXT
TO THEM BILLS?

04:25.626 --> 04:28.461
MAMA, UNLESS THAT BIBLE
GOT ABOUT $50,000

04:28.461 --> 04:31.097
TUCKED IN BETWEEN THE PAGES,
MAMA, I DON'T ‐‐

04:31.097 --> 04:32.132
[ SIGHS ]
I MEAN, I JUST DON'T SEE

04:32.132 --> 04:33.567
HOW THAT'S GONNA HELP
THE SITUATION.

04:33.567 --> 04:36.936
OOH, CHILD, THAT BIBLE IS
WORTH MORE THAN MONEY.

04:36.936 --> 04:40.240
I LOOK AT THOSE BILLS,
AND I GET WORRIED,

04:40.240 --> 04:41.975
AND I PICK UP THIS BIBLE,

04:41.975 --> 04:44.845
AND I READ ABOUT JOSEPH
AND ALL HE WENT THROUGH,

04:44.845 --> 04:47.514
OR MAYBE I READ ABOUT MOSES
AND EVERYTHING HE WENT THROUGH

04:47.514 --> 04:49.015
AND MAYBE A LITTLE BIT
ABOUT JOB.

04:49.015 --> 04:50.016
I GOT IT.

04:50.016 --> 04:51.518
YOU USED TO LOVE
TO GO TO CHURCH.

04:51.518 --> 04:53.086
MAMA, I WAS A KID BACK THEN.

04:53.086 --> 04:56.957
WELL, YOU STILL NEED TO GO
WITH ME SOMETIMES.

04:56.957 --> 04:58.324
DARCI ASKS ABOUT YOU
ALL THE TIME.

04:58.324 --> 04:59.660
WHO?

04:59.660 --> 05:03.336
DARCI, THAT PRETTY LITTLE GIRL
WHO USED TO LIKE YOU.

05:03.336 --> 05:05.405
[ SCOFFS ] YOU TALKING ABOUT
THE GIRL WITH THE BRACES

05:05.405 --> 05:06.439
AND THE HEADGEAR ON?

05:06.439 --> 05:08.474
‐[ LAUGHS ] NO, NO.
‐STOP IT.

05:08.474 --> 05:10.176
SHE DON'T LOOK LIKE
THAT NO MORE.

05:10.176 --> 05:12.078
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

05:12.078 --> 05:14.815
I'M GONNA ASK HER TO STOP OVER
HERE FOR DINNER AFTER CHURCH.

05:14.815 --> 05:15.882
NO, THANK YOU.

05:15.882 --> 05:18.151
[ LAUGHS ]

05:18.151 --> 05:21.054
OH, JUST 'CAUSE THAT LITTLE
FAST‐TAIL GIRL BROKE YOUR HEART

05:21.054 --> 05:22.856
DON'T MEAN
YOU SHOULD STOP DATING.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.357
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU BEEN ON A DATE?

05:24.357 --> 05:25.425
OOH, CHILD, PLEASE.

05:25.425 --> 05:27.227
[ LAUGHS ]

05:27.227 --> 05:28.829
CAN WE GET BACK TO THE SITUATION
AT HAND HERE, THOUGH,

05:28.829 --> 05:33.534
SERIOUSLY ‐‐
GETTING THESE BILLS PAID?

05:33.534 --> 05:36.336
WISH I COULD DO MORE,
MAMA, YOU KNOW?

05:36.336 --> 05:38.972
FELT LIKE ONCE
I GOT THIS TRUCK,

05:38.972 --> 05:42.008
THE MONEY WAS JUST GONNA START
ROLLING IN, YOU KNOW?

05:42.008 --> 05:44.511
IT TAKES A MINUTE
TO BUILD A DREAM, BABY.

05:44.511 --> 05:46.212
THE DREAM WAS GETTING
THIS TRUCK.

05:46.212 --> 05:48.849
NIGHTMARE IS TRYING TO GET
THIS BUSINESS GOING.

05:48.849 --> 05:51.384
‐YOU WILL.
‐I WANT TO HELP NOW, MAMA.

05:51.384 --> 05:52.953
YOU'RE NOT READY TO MOVE
BACK IN HERE WITH ME

05:52.953 --> 05:55.656
TO HELP ME PAY THESE BILLS.
WHAT ELSE YOU WANT TO DO?

05:57.190 --> 05:58.224
ROB A BANK.

05:58.224 --> 06:00.093
MNH‐MNH.
DON'T EVEN PLAY LIKE THAT.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.568
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:01.568 --> 06:02.669
I'M JUST KIDDING.

06:02.669 --> 06:04.971
I KNOW YOU ARE.

06:04.971 --> 06:08.642
BABY, GOD WILL ALWAYS
MAKE A WAY.

06:08.642 --> 06:10.110
I JUST WISH HE'D HURRY UP.

06:10.110 --> 06:12.012
MNH‐MNH.
WATCH YOUR MOUTH.

06:12.012 --> 06:13.814
SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN IT
LIKE THAT.

06:13.814 --> 06:16.116
JUST TIRED OF SEEING YOU TIRED
LIKE THIS, YOU KNOW?

06:16.116 --> 06:19.753
YOU JUST GOT OVER BEING SICK.

06:19.753 --> 06:23.724
BOY, I'VE BEEN WORKING SINCE
I WAS 9 YEARS OLD.

06:23.724 --> 06:27.127
I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO DO ANYTHING ELSE.

06:27.127 --> 06:28.962
AND YOU STOP TRYING
TO BABY ME.

06:28.962 --> 06:30.864
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU AIN'T YOUNG NO MORE.

06:30.864 --> 06:33.834
WHAT?
50 IS THE NEW 30!

06:33.834 --> 06:35.902
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

06:38.839 --> 06:40.674
YOU NEED TO STOP LISTENING
TO MY MUSIC.

06:40.674 --> 06:42.843
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

06:45.478 --> 06:47.581
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO
WITH YOUR DAY OFF?

06:47.581 --> 06:49.282
OH, WHEE.

06:49.282 --> 06:52.686
I'MMA CLEAN UP MY OWN HOUSE,
GO TO THE GROCERY STORE...

06:52.686 --> 06:53.787
OKAY.

06:53.787 --> 06:56.590
...MM, AND SLEEP.

06:56.590 --> 06:57.791
THAT SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN.

06:57.791 --> 06:59.926
MM‐HMM.
NOW GET OUT OF MY ROOM.

06:59.926 --> 07:01.134
[ GROANS ]

07:01.134 --> 07:02.803
[ CHUCKLES ]
YES, MA'AM.

07:02.803 --> 07:04.270
[ LAUGHS ]

07:04.270 --> 07:06.106
COME HERE.

07:06.106 --> 07:08.542
‐LOVE YOU.
‐LOVE YOU, TOO.

07:08.542 --> 07:09.876
WANT THE DOOR OPEN?

07:09.876 --> 07:11.144
OPEN OR CLOSED, MAMA.

07:11.144 --> 07:12.613
‐CLOSED.
‐OKAY.

07:12.613 --> 07:20.120
♪♪♪♪

07:20.120 --> 07:21.454
KATH, DEAR!

07:21.454 --> 07:23.857
Katheryn: IN HERE.

07:28.428 --> 07:29.763
WELL?

07:29.763 --> 07:30.797
WELL, WHAT?

07:30.797 --> 07:32.232
IS IT TRUE?

07:32.232 --> 07:33.466
IS WHAT TRUE?

07:33.466 --> 07:35.502
DON'T PLAY GAMES WITH ME,
KATHERYN CRYER.

07:35.502 --> 07:37.871
IS JIM RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR
OR WHAT?

07:37.871 --> 07:39.139
HE HASN'T DECIDED YET.

07:39.139 --> 07:40.674
WELL, WHAT IS HE
WAITING FOR?

07:40.674 --> 07:42.342
HE ENJOYS BEING A JUDGE.

07:42.342 --> 07:43.510
[ LAUGHS ]

07:43.510 --> 07:45.746
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.
LET'S SEE.

07:45.746 --> 07:48.114
A JUDGE OR A GOVERNOR.

07:48.114 --> 07:51.818
HMM. I'LL TAKE
THE GOVERNOR'S MANSION.

07:51.818 --> 07:53.086
COME ON.

07:53.086 --> 07:55.789
DON'T YOU WANT TO BE THE
FIRST LADY OF OUR GREAT STATE?

07:55.789 --> 07:58.692
I HAVE ENOUGH TO DEAL WITH
KEEPING MY FAMILY STRAIGHT.

07:58.692 --> 08:00.794
YOU HAVE TO GET EXCITED
ABOUT THIS,

08:00.794 --> 08:03.637
AND YOU HAVE TO GET HIM
EXCITED ABOUT IT.

08:03.637 --> 08:06.707
I'M NOT SURE THIS IS SOMETHING
MY FAMILY SHOULD BE INVOLVED IN.

08:06.707 --> 08:07.741
NONSENSE.

08:07.741 --> 08:09.976
DAVID AND I BOTH THINK
HE SHOULD RUN.

08:09.976 --> 08:11.211
IT'S HIS DECISION.

08:11.211 --> 08:13.213
IT'S NEVER
THE MAN'S DECISION.

08:13.213 --> 08:15.381
WE ALWAYS MAKE UP THEIR MINDS
FOR THEM.

08:15.381 --> 08:16.783
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

08:16.783 --> 08:22.689
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE WITH MY FIERY
FRIEND I ALWAYS KNEW AND LOVED?

08:22.689 --> 08:24.290
I HAVE NOTHING TO WEAR.

08:24.290 --> 08:26.159
[ SCOFFS ]
CALL SABRINA.

08:26.159 --> 08:27.628
‐VERONICA ‐‐
‐WHAT?

08:27.628 --> 08:31.865
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

08:31.865 --> 08:34.167
HOLD ON.

08:34.167 --> 08:36.069
KATHERYN CRYER...

08:36.069 --> 08:37.470
WHAT?

08:37.470 --> 08:41.107
...SOMETHING IS
GOING ON WITH YOU.

08:41.107 --> 08:42.943
NOTHING IS GOING ON.

08:42.943 --> 08:45.145
OUT WITH IT.

08:45.145 --> 08:48.815
I JUST TOLD YOU WHAT IT WAS.

08:48.815 --> 08:50.851
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

08:50.851 --> 08:53.654
YES, I DID.

08:53.654 --> 08:56.990
HMM. I HAVE KNOWN YOU
LONG ENOUGH TO KNOW

08:56.990 --> 08:59.025
WHEN THERE'S SOMETHING
GOING ON WITH YOU,

08:59.025 --> 09:02.703
OTHER THAN WHAT'S IN THE AIR.

09:02.703 --> 09:04.304
I AM FINE.

09:04.304 --> 09:06.139
THIS IS NOT LIKE YOU,
KATHERYN.

09:06.139 --> 09:07.508
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

09:07.508 --> 09:10.143
WHEN YOU HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY,
YOU SAY IT.

09:10.143 --> 09:13.213
YOU DON'T MINCE WORDS.

09:13.213 --> 09:15.015
YOU NEED TO GO BACK TO WORK.

09:15.015 --> 09:16.416
I'M RETIRED.

09:16.416 --> 09:19.886
WELL, THAT BULLDOG ATTORNEY
IN YOU IS OFF TO THE RACES.

09:19.886 --> 09:22.155
THAT'S BECAUSE THIS ATTORNEY

09:22.155 --> 09:25.425
IS PICKING UP A SCENT
OF SOMETHING.

09:25.425 --> 09:29.262
YOU ARE OFF SCENT
AND OFF YOUR ROCKER.

09:29.262 --> 09:33.199
WELL, A FEW MONTHS AGO, YOU
WOULD HAVE SOLD YOUR CHILDREN

09:33.199 --> 09:34.668
TO BE IN
THE GOVERNOR'S MANSION.

09:34.668 --> 09:38.004
AND NOW, ALL OF A SUDDEN,

09:38.004 --> 09:40.574
YOU CAN'T DECIDE WHAT TO DO?

09:43.443 --> 09:45.345
A LOT CAN CHANGE
IN A COUPLE OF MONTHS.

09:45.345 --> 09:46.647
LIKE WHAT?

09:46.647 --> 09:50.383
I'M NOT ON THE STAND HERE,
VERONICA.

09:50.383 --> 09:52.485
OKAY, OKAY.

09:52.485 --> 09:55.488
I'LL LET IT GO.

09:55.488 --> 09:56.957
THANK YOU.

09:56.957 --> 10:01.735
BUT EVENTUALLY YOU WILL TELL ME
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO HIDE.

10:01.735 --> 10:05.806
AND EVENTUALLY YOU WILL GET IT
THROUGH THAT CRAZY HEAD OF YOURS

10:05.806 --> 10:09.242
THAT I AM NOT TRYING
TO HIDE SOMETHING.

10:15.749 --> 10:18.852
I THOUGHT WE WERE BETTER FRIENDS
THAN THIS, KATHERYN.

10:22.222 --> 10:23.824
WE ARE.

10:26.392 --> 10:28.829
I JUST NEED YOU
TO LET THIS GO.

10:31.497 --> 10:33.066
OKAY.

10:33.066 --> 10:37.804
SO, ARE WE GONNA CALL SABRINA
ABOUT THE DRESS?

10:37.804 --> 10:40.206
‐YES.
‐GOOD.

10:40.206 --> 10:42.142
I HAVE HER NUMBER SOMEWHERE.

10:42.142 --> 10:43.577
I WILL GET IT BACK TO YOU.

10:43.577 --> 10:45.879
IT'S JUST NOT
THAT IMPORTANT TO ME.

10:45.879 --> 10:47.548
NOT THAT IMPORTANT?

10:47.548 --> 10:50.617
HE COULD BE GOVERNOR, MAYBE EVEN
PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES.

10:50.617 --> 10:52.152
OKAY, VERONICA, ENOUGH.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.754
YOU HAVE TO CONVINCE HIM!

10:53.754 --> 10:55.922
[ SIGHS ]

10:55.922 --> 10:57.724
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH DAVID

10:57.724 --> 10:59.259
TRYING TO BE
LIEUTENANT GOVERNOR.

10:59.259 --> 11:00.661
OF COURSE.

11:00.661 --> 11:03.504
IF JIM RUNS, THEN HE'LL HAVE
TO HAVE DAVID ON THE TICKET.

11:03.504 --> 11:04.671
IT JUST MAKES SENSE.

11:04.671 --> 11:06.139
VERONICA,

11:06.139 --> 11:10.043
WHEN SOMEONE RUNS FOR OFFICE,
ALL THEIR DIRTY LITTLE SECRETS

11:10.043 --> 11:12.345
JUST COME RELUCTANTLY
OUT OF THE CLOSET.

11:12.345 --> 11:15.315
WHAT SECRETS
COULD JIM POSSIBLY HAVE?

11:23.657 --> 11:32.398
♪♪♪♪

11:32.398 --> 11:41.141
♪♪♪♪

11:41.141 --> 11:42.509
[ SIGHS ]

11:42.509 --> 11:48.148
♪♪♪♪

11:48.148 --> 11:53.787
♪♪♪♪

11:53.787 --> 11:55.722
THERE YOU ARE.

11:55.722 --> 11:56.857
I'M NOT JIM.

11:56.857 --> 11:58.625
OH.

11:58.625 --> 12:00.594
HI.

12:00.594 --> 12:03.604
GET OUT OF HIS CHAIR.

12:03.604 --> 12:05.371
WHERE IS HE?

12:05.371 --> 12:07.173
HE'S IN COURT.

12:07.173 --> 12:09.876
I'LL BE TAKING CARE OF THIS.

12:09.876 --> 12:13.413
TAKING CARE OF WHAT?

12:13.413 --> 12:15.381
DON'T PLAY GAMES WITH ME,
YOUNG LADY.

12:15.381 --> 12:16.783
I'M NOT JIM.

12:16.783 --> 12:19.052
YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

12:19.052 --> 12:21.054
YOU'RE BETTER LOOKING.

12:24.224 --> 12:28.428
I WANT TO BE ASSURED THAT ONCE
OUR TRANSACTION IS COMPLETE,

12:28.428 --> 12:31.932
YOU WILL NEVER SEE
MY CLIENT AGAIN.

12:31.932 --> 12:33.534
YOUR CLIENT?

12:33.534 --> 12:37.804
WOW. SO OFFICIAL.

12:37.804 --> 12:39.740
THIS IS NOT A PAYOFF.

12:39.740 --> 12:44.010
THIS IS A SCHOLARSHIP
