25:53.419 --> 25:55.889
CAN CAUSE YOU TO CALL
A FEW THINGS INTO QUESTION,

25:55.889 --> 25:58.525
AND I KNOW YOU'RE GOING THROUGH
A BIT OF A MIDLIFE CRISIS.

25:58.525 --> 26:01.027
BUT NOW IS NOT THE TIME
TO SIT DOWN AND QUIT.

26:01.027 --> 26:04.671
NOW IS THE TIME
TO BUCKLE DOWN AND FIGHT,

26:04.671 --> 26:08.241
'CAUSE SOMETIMES WE HAVE TO
SACRIFICE OUR MOMENTARY DESIRES

26:08.241 --> 26:11.411
ON THE ALTAR OF DESTINY.

26:11.411 --> 26:15.982
YOU SHOULD BE GOVERNOR.

26:15.982 --> 26:18.084
FOUR YEARS AFTER YOU.

26:18.084 --> 26:20.053
EIGHT.

26:20.053 --> 26:22.556
SO THAT MEANS YOU'RE RUNNING?

26:22.556 --> 26:24.791
DAVID, I PROMISE THAT YOU'LL
BE THE FIRST TO KNOW

26:24.791 --> 26:26.627
WHEN I'VE MADE MY DECISION.

26:26.627 --> 26:31.064
♪♪♪♪

26:37.604 --> 26:40.774
CAN I TELL YOU HOW GOOD IT FEELS
TO FINALLY HAVE A DAY OFF?

26:40.774 --> 26:42.576
PHEW! SOME DAY OFF.

26:42.576 --> 26:45.478
NOW I GOT TO LEARN HOW
TO MAKE LENTIL SOUP.

26:45.478 --> 26:47.480
WELL, JUST BECAUSE
I'M GOING ON VACATION

26:47.480 --> 26:49.950
AND YOU NEED TO LEARN
HOW TO MAKE IT.

26:49.950 --> 26:51.451
AND, BY THE WAY,
NO SALT AT ALL.

26:51.451 --> 26:54.420
‐OH, COME ON.
‐NO. SHE DOESN'T LIKE IT.

26:54.420 --> 26:55.756
SOMETHING ‐‐
YOU KNOW THAT FAMILY NEEDS

26:55.756 --> 26:57.624
A LITTLE SEASONING
OR SOMETHING.

26:57.624 --> 26:58.625
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:58.625 --> 27:00.527
I WISH I COULD GO
ON VACATION.

27:00.527 --> 27:02.302
BUT I NEED TO WORK
AS MUCH AS I CAN.

27:02.302 --> 27:03.804
YOU'RE STILL BEHIND
ON YOUR BILLS?

27:03.804 --> 27:05.506
YES, BUT IT'S GETTING BETTER.

27:05.506 --> 27:06.807
MM.

27:06.807 --> 27:08.308
‐GUESS WHAT?
‐WHAT?

27:08.308 --> 27:10.176
MY HUMBERTO GOT A RAISE.

27:10.176 --> 27:11.778
YEAH, SO I CAN RELAX.

27:11.778 --> 27:14.648
OH, REALLY?
THAT'S GOOD.

27:14.648 --> 27:15.849
SEE?

27:15.849 --> 27:18.118
I'M SO HAPPY
THAT YOU'RE HAPPY FOR ME.

27:18.118 --> 27:20.320
OF COURSE I AM.
WHY WOULDN'T I BE?

27:20.320 --> 27:22.422
WELL, THERE'S A LOT OF PEOPLE
THAT ARE NOT HAPPY

27:22.422 --> 27:23.356
WHEN YOU DO WELL.

27:23.356 --> 27:25.458
OOH, GIRL, DON'T I KNOW IT.

27:25.458 --> 27:26.827
[ LAUGHS ]

27:26.827 --> 27:28.529
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

27:28.529 --> 27:30.897
WHO IS THAT?

27:30.897 --> 27:32.533
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

27:32.533 --> 27:34.935
UH‐OH.

27:34.935 --> 27:35.969
IT'S KATHERYN.

27:35.969 --> 27:37.170
DON'T ANSWER IT.

27:37.170 --> 27:40.774
‐I HAVE TO.
‐NO!

27:40.774 --> 27:43.443
HANNA, KATHERYN CALLING US ON
OUR DAY OFF CAN'T BE GOOD.

27:43.443 --> 27:44.410
IT'S FINE.

27:44.410 --> 27:46.647
DON'T ANSWER IT!

27:46.647 --> 27:48.649
HELLO?

27:48.649 --> 27:52.586
I'M GOOD.
HOW ARE YOU, MRS. CRYER?

27:52.586 --> 27:55.355
OH, OKAY.

27:55.355 --> 27:56.823
SURE.
I'LL COME IN RIGHT NOW.

27:56.823 --> 28:00.160
BUT IT'S GONNA TAKE ME A MINUTE
'CAUSE OF THE BUS SCHEDULE.

28:00.160 --> 28:01.735
OKAY.

28:01.735 --> 28:03.336
NO PROBLEM.

28:03.336 --> 28:04.605
I'M ON MY WAY.

28:04.605 --> 28:06.172
ALL RIGHT.

28:06.172 --> 28:08.709
CELINE?

28:08.709 --> 28:11.912
SHE'S HERE WITH ME RIGHT NOW.

28:11.912 --> 28:14.615
YES, I SURE WILL.
I'LL TELL HER.

28:14.615 --> 28:16.550
OKAY, WE'LL SEE YOU IN A BIT.

28:16.550 --> 28:17.918
ALL RIGHT.
BYE‐BYE.

28:17.918 --> 28:20.286
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ]
HOW COULD YOU DO THAT?

28:20.286 --> 28:21.922
YOU ARE SO WRONG, HONESTLY.

28:21.922 --> 28:23.323
I'M SORRY.
COME ON NOW.

28:23.323 --> 28:25.225
‐IT'S OUR DAY OFF!
‐SHE'S GOT SOMETHING GOING ON.

28:25.225 --> 28:26.693
‐COME ON.
‐RIGHT.

28:26.693 --> 28:28.161
[ KNOCK AT DOOR ]

28:28.161 --> 28:29.730
[ Laughing ]
JUST A MINUTE.

28:29.730 --> 28:30.964
‐COME ON.
‐I HATE YOU.

28:30.964 --> 28:32.599
GO GET THE DOOR.

28:37.137 --> 28:38.138
HEY.

28:38.138 --> 28:40.173
I'M LOOKING
FOR BENJAMIN YOUNG.

28:40.173 --> 28:41.542
WELL, HE'S NOT HERE
RIGHT NOW.

28:41.542 --> 28:42.509
WHAT'S GOING ON?

28:42.509 --> 28:43.944
THIS IS A FORECLOSURE NOTICE.

28:43.944 --> 28:47.213
YOU WILL HAVE SEVEN DAYS
TO VACATE THE PREMISES.

28:47.213 --> 28:50.951
NOW WAIT A MINUTE. THIS HAS GOT
TO BE SOME KIND OF MISTAKE.

28:50.951 --> 28:56.256
♪♪♪♪

28:56.256 --> 28:58.258
WHAT?

28:58.258 --> 29:02.836
♪♪♪♪

29:02.836 --> 29:04.170
Katheryn:
I AM SORRY, HANNA.

29:04.170 --> 29:05.972
I KNOW I TOLD YOU YOU COULD
HAVE THE DAY OFF.

29:05.972 --> 29:07.508
BUT JIM JUST SPRANG THIS ON ME.

29:07.508 --> 29:08.675
IT'S FINE.

29:08.675 --> 29:10.877
CELINE, I NEED YOU
TO MAKE SURE THAT THE CAVIAR

29:10.877 --> 29:12.112
IS NOT BRUISED.

29:12.112 --> 29:14.080
I NEED SOAP IN
ALL THE POWDER ROOMS.

29:14.080 --> 29:15.782
PLEASE MAKE SURE
THERE IS FRESH FLOWERS

29:15.782 --> 29:17.751
IN ALL THE OTHER ROOMS.

29:17.751 --> 29:20.386
OH, JIM MADE A MESS
THIS MORNING.

29:20.386 --> 29:22.222
PLEASE MAKE SURE
THAT'S CLEANED UP.

29:25.992 --> 29:30.330
OOH, SOME SURPRISE
ON OUR DAY OFF, HUH?

29:30.330 --> 29:32.498
HEY. HANNA...

29:32.498 --> 29:35.168
♪♪♪♪

29:35.168 --> 29:37.638
YOU OKAY?

29:37.638 --> 29:40.907
YEAH.

29:40.907 --> 29:43.844
I‐I WISH I HAD THE MONEY
TO LEND YOU, BUT I DON'T.

29:43.844 --> 29:46.713
[ Voice breaking ] I WASN'T
GONNA ASK YOU FOR MONEY.

29:49.816 --> 29:52.753
I THOUGHT THE HOUSE
WAS IN YOUR SON'S NAME.

29:52.753 --> 29:55.856
IT IS.

29:55.856 --> 29:59.626
HE MUST HAVE TAKEN OUT
THE MORTGAGE.

29:59.626 --> 30:03.169
I'M SO SORRY.

30:03.169 --> 30:05.572
LISTEN, HE PROBABLY
HAS A GOOD REASON.

30:05.572 --> 30:09.309
NO, SEE, I WOULD HAVE
EXPECTED THIS FROM CANDACE,

30:09.309 --> 30:12.145
BUT NOT BENNY.

30:12.145 --> 30:15.148
HE'S A GOOD BOY.

30:15.148 --> 30:16.950
WELL, DON'T ‐‐
DON'T DO THAT, HUH?

30:16.950 --> 30:18.919
DON'T JUMP TO CONCLUSIONS
YOU DON'T KNOW.

30:18.919 --> 30:20.320
WAIT TILL YOU FIND OUT
THE TRUTH.

30:20.320 --> 30:22.523
I KNOW THE TRUTH.

30:22.523 --> 30:25.626
I KNOW THE TRUTH.

30:25.626 --> 30:28.795
HE MORTGAGED MY HOUSE.

30:28.795 --> 30:31.231
I JUST WANT TO KNOW WHY.

30:31.231 --> 30:34.968
I MEAN, WHY WOULD HE
DO THIS, CELINE, WHY?

30:34.968 --> 30:36.169
OH, GOD.

30:36.169 --> 30:38.739
I JUST GOT TO KNOW WHY.

30:38.739 --> 30:39.906
I KNOW YOU DO, BUT RIGHT NOW,

30:39.906 --> 30:41.642
WE HAVE TO GET
A LOT OF THINGS READY, OKAY?

30:41.642 --> 30:43.309
‐MM‐HMM.
‐COME ON.

30:43.309 --> 30:49.182
LORD JESUS.
LORD JESUS, HELP ME, JESUS.

30:49.182 --> 30:50.784
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.
COME ON.

30:50.784 --> 30:54.655
‐[ EXHALES SLOWLY ]
‐IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

30:54.655 --> 30:56.089
COME ON.
LET'S GET EVERYTHING READY.

30:56.089 --> 30:57.423
OKAY.

30:57.423 --> 30:59.359
[ SIGHS ]

31:05.338 --> 31:08.642
SO, HAVE YOU DECIDED WHAT DRESS
YOU WERE GOING TO WEAR?

31:08.642 --> 31:10.811
NO. I'VE GOT
A CALL INTO FRANCINE.

31:10.811 --> 31:12.679
WE'VE GOT TO SEE WHAT
SHE CAN COME UP WITH.

31:12.679 --> 31:15.181
A LITTLE SCARY, BUT YOU'VE GOT
TO SEE WHAT SHE COMES UP WITH.

31:15.181 --> 31:16.482
‐[ LAUGHS ]
‐YOU SHOULD BE CALLING HER.

31:16.482 --> 31:18.685
WELL, THAT'S...

31:18.685 --> 31:20.821
SON.

31:20.821 --> 31:21.855
MOM.

31:21.855 --> 31:24.090
HOW ARE YOU?

31:24.090 --> 31:26.560
I'M GREAT.

31:26.560 --> 31:29.062
HELLO, WYATT.
HOW ARE YOU?

31:29.062 --> 31:30.997
FINE.

31:30.997 --> 31:32.498
YOU LOOK WELL.

31:32.498 --> 31:33.867
THANKS.

31:33.867 --> 31:36.102
HELLO, SON.

31:36.102 --> 31:37.303
MOM.

31:37.303 --> 31:39.372
HUG YOUR MOTHER.

31:39.372 --> 31:42.342
OH, OF COURSE.

31:42.342 --> 31:43.810
LOOK AT YOU.

31:43.810 --> 31:46.179
I SEE THAT SPARKLE
IN YOUR EYES.

31:46.179 --> 31:48.849
HE'S BEEN GREAT.
WORKING OUT EVERY DAY.

31:51.184 --> 31:53.019
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

31:53.019 --> 31:55.656
I'M GLAD YOU CHOSE OUR PLACE.

31:55.656 --> 31:58.191
SEE, KATHERYN?
I TOLD YOU IT WOULD BE GREAT.

31:58.191 --> 31:59.860
I KNEW IT WOULD WORK FOR HIM.

31:59.860 --> 32:01.467
YOU WERE RIGHT.

32:01.467 --> 32:02.803
SO, WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

32:02.803 --> 32:04.805
WHY DID I HAVE TO DRIVE
FOUR HOURS?

32:04.805 --> 32:06.940
WELL, HOLD ON.

32:06.940 --> 32:08.742
WE'RE WAITING FOR YOUR SISTER
AND YOUR FATHER.

32:08.742 --> 32:13.079
HE WENT TO PICK HER UP.
HE SHOULD BE HERE ANY MINUTE.

32:13.079 --> 32:14.815
MNH‐MNH.
NO, NO.

32:17.083 --> 32:20.120
I'D LIKE TO SIT
NEXT TO WYATT.

32:21.722 --> 32:23.456
JEFFERY, WHAT IS THAT
YOU'RE WEARING?

32:23.456 --> 32:26.026
OH, IT'S ‐‐
IT'S JUST A BRACELET.

32:26.026 --> 32:28.829
WELL, TAKE IT OFF BEFORE
YOUR FATHER SEES IT.

32:28.829 --> 32:30.296
IT'S JUST A BRACELET.

32:30.296 --> 32:33.133
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT?

32:33.133 --> 32:35.936
I GAVE IT TO HIM.

32:35.936 --> 32:38.438
WHY WOULD YOU GIVE HIM
A BRACELET?

32:40.941 --> 32:42.909
IS THIS THE BRACELET YOUR
GRANDFATHER GAVE YOU?

32:42.909 --> 32:47.280
YEAH. WHY THE HELL
WOULD I WANT IT?

32:47.280 --> 32:50.584
TAKE IT OFF.

32:50.584 --> 32:52.152
IT'S JUST A BRACELET.

32:52.152 --> 32:53.820
Jeffery: NO, NO, NO.
IT'S ‐‐ IT'S FINE, WYATT.

32:53.820 --> 32:54.988
MY DAD DOESN'T LIKE ME
WEARING STUFF LIKE THAT.

32:54.988 --> 32:57.558
THEN WHY THE HELL DID
YOU TAKE IT FROM ME?

32:57.558 --> 32:59.392
HELLO, HELLO.

32:59.392 --> 33:00.393
DARLING.

33:00.393 --> 33:02.736
‐MOM.
‐HELLO, HONEY.

33:02.736 --> 33:04.104
WYATT.

33:04.104 --> 33:06.106
HI, VERONICA, JEFFERY.

33:06.106 --> 33:08.274
HELLO, SWEETHEART.

33:08.274 --> 33:10.944
SO, WHAT'S GOING ON?
I'M ON THE EDGE OF MY SEAT.

33:10.944 --> 33:13.614
WE RODE ALL THE WAY HERE,
AND HE DIDN'T SAY A WORD.

33:13.614 --> 33:15.015
WHAT'S GOING ON?

33:15.015 --> 33:17.250
YEAH. THE ONLY TIME WE DO
THESE FAMILY MEETINGS

33:17.250 --> 33:18.585
IS WHEN I'M IN TROUBLE.

33:18.585 --> 33:20.020
OR ME.

33:20.020 --> 33:21.254
YOU'RE NEVER IN TROUBLE.

33:21.254 --> 33:22.623
Katheryn:
NO ONE IS IN TROUBLE.

33:22.623 --> 33:25.726
YOUR FATHER HAS SOMETHING
HE'D LIKE TO SAY.

33:25.726 --> 33:26.727
YES, THANK YOU.

33:26.727 --> 33:29.329
UM, I THOUGHT IT WAS IMPORTANT

33:29.329 --> 33:32.198
TO HAVE MY ENTIRE FAMILY
TOGETHER.

33:32.198 --> 33:34.334
‐I KNOW WHAT THIS IS.
‐[ LAUGHS ]

33:34.334 --> 33:36.469
YES, I THOUGHT IT WAS IMPORTANT
TO GATHER EVERYONE ‐‐

33:36.469 --> 33:38.572
MY FAMILY, MY LOVED ONES,
MY DEAR FRIENDS ‐‐

33:38.572 --> 33:41.474
BECAUSE, WELL,
I'VE DECIDED TO ‐‐

33:41.474 --> 33:43.309
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

33:43.309 --> 33:44.945
WHO COULD THAT BE?

33:44.945 --> 33:46.513
EVERYONE'S HERE, RIGHT?

33:46.513 --> 33:48.649
MAYBE ANOTHER LOVED ONE.

33:54.521 --> 33:58.559
♪♪♪♪

33:58.559 --> 34:00.360
WHO IS IT, HANNA?

34:00.360 --> 34:06.306
♪♪♪♪

34:06.306 --> 34:08.441
HI.

34:08.441 --> 34:11.311
HI!

34:11.311 --> 34:14.314
AMANDA, LOOK WHO'S HERE.

34:14.314 --> 34:17.518
♪♪♪♪

34:17.518 --> 34:18.852
I'M SORRY I'M LATE.

34:18.852 --> 34:21.087
GETTING A CAB IN THIS TOWN
IS AWFUL.

34:21.087 --> 34:24.758
I HAVE GOT TO GET A CAR.

34:24.758 --> 34:26.793
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

34:26.793 --> 34:28.695
Amanda: I INVITED HER.

34:28.695 --> 34:30.531
IS THAT OKAY?

34:33.033 --> 34:35.869
AMANDA,
THIS IS A PRIVATE MOMENT.

34:35.869 --> 34:40.541
YES, THIS IS, UH, JUST FOR
FAMILY, SWEETHEART.

34:40.541 --> 34:45.045
WELL, THIS IS AN
ECCENTRIC‐LOOKING FAMILY.

34:45.045 --> 34:47.948
I WANTED HER TO COME, OKAY?

34:47.948 --> 34:50.183
SURE, IT'S FINE.

34:50.183 --> 34:51.785
HAVE A SEAT, CANDACE.

34:51.785 --> 34:53.920
WOULD YOU LIKE SOMETHING
TO DRINK?

34:53.920 --> 34:55.488
YES.

34:55.488 --> 35:00.927
HANNA ‐‐ THAT'S YOUR
MAID'S NAME, RIGHT?

35:00.927 --> 35:04.671
HANNA, CAN I HAVE SOME
SPARKLING WATER, PLEASE?

35:06.940 --> 35:08.775
THANK YOU.

35:08.775 --> 35:14.280
♪♪♪♪

35:14.280 --> 35:19.820
♪♪♪♪

35:19.820 --> 35:21.722
GIRL IS OUT OF HER DAMN MIND.

35:21.722 --> 35:23.757
[ SIGHS ]

35:23.757 --> 35:26.426
‐I CAN'T DO IT. I CAN'T DO IT.
‐YES, YOU CAN.

35:26.426 --> 35:29.195
NOW I'M GONNA HAVE TO GO BACK
OUT THERE AND TELL THEM PEOPLE.

35:29.195 --> 35:31.765
[ Voice breaking ] DID YOU
HEAR WHAT SHE SAID TO ME?

35:31.765 --> 35:34.200
THAT GIRL IS...

35:34.200 --> 35:35.301
Shh! NO.
JUST CALM DOWN.

35:35.301 --> 35:36.603
YOU'RE JUST UPSET ABOUT
EVERYTHING, HONEY.

35:36.603 --> 35:37.470
IT'S TOO MUCH!

35:37.470 --> 35:39.439
‐IT'S TOO MUCH.
‐I KNOW.

35:39.439 --> 35:40.907
Amanda: COME ON, DAD.
TELL US.

35:40.907 --> 35:42.976
I ALREADY KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA SAY, SO SAY IT.

35:42.976 --> 35:45.278
JIM?

35:45.278 --> 35:48.815
I HAVE DECIDED
TO RUN FOR GOVERNOR.

35:48.815 --> 35:50.316
[ Laughing ]
I KNEW IT!

35:50.316 --> 35:53.153
I KNEW IT.
OH, DAD, THAT'S GREAT, DAD.

35:53.153 --> 35:56.089
‐DIDN'T I TELL YOU, CANDACE?
‐YOU SURE DID.

35:56.089 --> 35:59.225
WELL, WE NEED TO GET THE
CHAMPAGNE AND TOAST TO YOU.

35:59.225 --> 36:03.570
HOLD ON, HOLD ON.
WHY ARE WE CELEBRATING THIS?

36:03.570 --> 36:05.238
BECAUSE THIS IS A GOOD THING.

36:05.238 --> 36:09.275
HAVE WE NOT FORGOTTEN HOW REALLY
SCREWED UP THIS FAMILY IS?

36:09.275 --> 36:10.811
SO I WAS SUMMONED DOWN HERE

36:10.811 --> 36:12.913
TO BE TOLD
YOU'RE RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR?

36:12.913 --> 36:16.349
I'VE HAD ENOUGH SCRUTINY GROWING
UP WITH THIS LAST NAME.

36:16.349 --> 36:19.419
THIS IS JUST GREAT.

36:19.419 --> 36:22.188
JUST GREAT.

36:22.188 --> 36:24.057
COME ON, JEFFERY.

36:24.057 --> 36:25.859
GO ON, SON.

36:28.228 --> 36:29.696
I LOVE YOU.

36:29.696 --> 36:31.532
OH, YEAH.
I‐I LOVE YOU, TOO, MOM.

36:31.532 --> 36:32.933
AND GOOD NIGHT.

36:34.868 --> 36:36.570
WELL, I'M HAPPY
YOU'RE RUNNING.

36:36.570 --> 36:37.938
YEAH, I AM, TOO.

36:37.938 --> 36:41.007
[ CHUCKLES ]
CONGRATULATIONS.

36:43.910 --> 36:45.879
WYATT, YOU HAVE GOT TO STOP
FLYING OFF THE HANDLE LIKE THIS.

36:45.879 --> 36:47.347
DON'T TELL ME TO STOP
FLYING OFF THE HANDLE.

36:47.347 --> 36:48.649
WHAT IS IT THIS TIME?

36:48.649 --> 36:50.884
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA WHAT
THIS WILL DO TO THIS FAMILY?

36:50.884 --> 36:52.085
THIS IS A GOOD THING!

36:52.085 --> 36:53.687
NO, IT ISN'T.

36:53.687 --> 36:56.489
THIS IS ABSOLUTELY
GONNA DESTROY THIS FAMILY.

36:56.489 --> 36:58.058
HOW SO?

36:58.058 --> 36:59.560
HOW SO?

36:59.560 --> 37:03.202
LOOK AT YOU, WEARING THESE
ROSE‐COLORED GLASSES,

37:03.202 --> 37:07.040
ACTING LIKE YOUR GLASS
IS ALWAYS HALF‐FULL.

37:07.040 --> 37:08.975
YOU JUST HAVE NO IDEA, MAN.

37:08.975 --> 37:11.077
I'M LOST ON THIS ONE.

37:11.077 --> 37:12.746
YOU'RE SO SELFISH.

37:12.746 --> 37:15.982
AND DON'T YOU THINK IT'S SELFISH
TO NOT STAND WITH YOUR FATHER?

37:15.982 --> 37:17.216
[ SCOFFS ] NO.

37:17.216 --> 37:18.084
NO?

37:18.084 --> 37:20.821
NO, NOT AT ALL.

37:20.821 --> 37:23.056
OKAY, THIS IS BEYOND ME.

37:23.056 --> 37:26.359
WELL, MY FATHER ‐‐
HE'S NO CHOIRBOY.

37:26.359 --> 37:31.331
MY SISTER ‐‐ SHE CAN'T HANDLE
ANY KIND OF PRESSURE.

37:31.331 --> 37:33.199
AND THEN THERE'S MY MOTHER...

37:33.199 --> 37:34.568
[SCOFFS]

37:34.568 --> 37:38.972
...WHO'S LIVING IN SOME
KIND OF FANTASY LAND.

37:38.972 --> 37:42.609
GO ON.
YOU FORGOT TO MENTION YOU.

37:42.609 --> 37:44.711
WHY AM I EVEN TALKING TO YOU?

37:46.346 --> 37:47.948
‐CALM DOWN, OKAY?
‐CALM DOWN?

37:47.948 --> 37:49.315
THIS IS GONNA BE OKAY, WYATT.

37:49.315 --> 37:50.584
I THINK YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

37:50.584 --> 37:51.618
OVERREACTING?

37:51.618 --> 37:53.019
YES!

37:53.019 --> 37:58.424
WELL, LET'S SEE WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN THE WHOLE STATE OF GEORGIA

37:58.424 --> 38:04.004
FINDS OUT THEIR
FUTURE GOVERNOR, JIM CRYER,

38:04.004 --> 38:07.207
IS SLEEPING WITH CANDACE.

38:07.207 --> 38:08.709
HUH?

38:08.709 --> 38:10.544
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

38:10.544 --> 38:12.679
I SAW THEM.

38:12.679 --> 38:14.815
YOU SAW THEM DOING WHAT?

38:14.815 --> 38:20.453
I SAW THEM GO INTO THE STUDY,
TOGETHER.

38:20.453 --> 38:23.624
WERE THEY HAVING SEX?

38:23.624 --> 38:24.725
I DON'T KNOW.

38:24.725 --> 38:27.628
BUT I SAW THEM GO
INTO THE STUDY TOGETHER,

38:27.628 --> 38:29.395
AND THE DOOR CLOSED,

38:29.395 --> 38:32.098
AND THEY WERE IN THERE
FOR A LONG TIME.

38:32.098 --> 38:33.700
OKAY.

38:33.700 --> 38:35.636
WELL, THAT DOESN'T MEAN
ANYTHING, WYATT.

38:35.636 --> 38:38.371
‐ARE YOU AN IDIOT?
‐NO. ARE YOU AN IDIOT?

38:38.371 --> 38:40.073
IF YOU'RE GONNA COME WITH
THOSE KIND OF ALLEGATIONS,

38:40.073 --> 38:41.407
YOU BETTER HAVE SOME PROOF.

38:41.407 --> 38:43.944
MM. PROOF.

38:43.944 --> 38:46.412
I'M GOOD AT GETTING PROOF,

38:46.412 --> 38:50.383
LIKE THE PROOF
I HAVE ABOUT YOU.

38:50.383 --> 38:52.619
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

38:52.619 --> 38:54.454
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

38:54.454 --> 38:56.256
IT'S MY "GET OUT
OF JAIL FREE" CARD.

38:56.256 --> 38:58.391
I CAN USE IT WHEN I NEED IT.

38:58.391 --> 39:03.604
♪♪♪♪

39:03.604 --> 39:07.107
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

39:07.107 --> 39:11.344
OKAY, MR. WYATT.

39:11.344 --> 39:14.347
OKAY.

39:14.347 --> 39:16.983
I'M SORRY.
I HAVE TO GO.

39:16.983 --> 39:18.885
Katheryn: WILL YOU BE STAYING
FOR DINNER, CANDACE?

39:18.885 --> 39:20.921
NO.
I HAVE AN APPOINTMENT.

39:20.921 --> 39:22.789
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I HAVE TO GO NOW.

39:22.789 --> 39:24.224
CAN I CALL THE CAB?

39:24.224 --> 39:25.759
WAIT. I THOUGHT
YOU WERE STAYING.

39:25.759 --> 39:28.194
I WISH I COULD, BUT I HAVE
A VERY IMPORTANT MEETING,

39:28.194 --> 39:29.996
AND IF I'M NOT THERE,

39:29.996 --> 39:34.668
IT COULD CHANGE
A LOT OF PEOPLE'S LIVES.

39:34.668 --> 39:37.804
WELL, THAT'S SOME PRESSURE
FOR A COLLEGE STUDENT.

39:37.804 --> 39:40.473
INDEED.
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:40.473 --> 39:41.575
WELL, NEXT TIME.

39:41.575 --> 39:43.343
OKAY.
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

39:43.343 --> 39:44.978
UM, I'M SORRY, EVERYBODY.

39:44.978 --> 39:46.747
CONGRATULATIONS, MR. CRYER.

39:46.747 --> 39:48.481
[ LAUGHS ]

39:48.481 --> 39:50.216
WHERE'S THAT MAID OF YOURS?

39:50.216 --> 39:52.653
CAN SHE MAYBE
CALL A CAB FOR ME?

39:52.653 --> 39:53.887
[ SIGHS ]
POSSIBLY, YES.

39:53.887 --> 39:55.956
THANK YOU.

39:55.956 --> 39:59.092
I HAVE TO GET BACK TO THE
OFFICE, SWEETHEART.

39:59.092 --> 40:02.869
♪♪♪♪

40:02.869 --> 40:06.206
IS, UH, NO ONE STAYING
FOR DINNER?

40:06.206 --> 40:08.174
I CALLED THE STAFF IN
ON THEIR DAY OFF.

40:08.174 --> 40:09.910
UM...

40:09.910 --> 40:11.377
IT'S FINE.

40:11.377 --> 40:14.881
WE'LL CELEBRATE WITH YOU, JIM.

40:14.881 --> 40:17.684
OH, KATHERYN,
THE TABLE LOOKS AMAZING.

40:17.684 --> 40:19.185
ARE THOSE AMARYLLIS?

40:19.185 --> 40:21.988
YES. PLANTED THEM
IN THE GARDEN.

40:21.988 --> 40:28.662
♪♪♪♪

40:28.662 --> 40:35.335
♪♪♪♪

40:35.335 --> 40:37.504
[ SIGHS ]

40:37.504 --> 40:41.207
♪♪♪♪

40:41.207 --> 40:43.443
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:43.443 --> 40:46.647
OKAY, JIM.

40:46.647 --> 40:48.582
OKAY.

40:48.582 --> 40:57.023
♪♪♪♪

40:57.023 --> 41:05.438
♪♪♪♪

41:05.438 --> 41:07.373
HELLO, ROSE?

41:07.373 --> 41:09.242
HI. THIS IS CANDACE.

41:09.242 --> 41:11.377
I WAS TALKING TO YOU TODAY

41:11.377 --> 41:14.080
ABOUT THE WORK YOU DO
WITH ABUSED ANIMALS.

41:14.080 --> 41:17.984
WELL, ACTUALLY, THAT'S NOT WHAT
I WANTED TO SPEAK TO YOU ABOUT.

41:17.984 --> 41:23.757
I HAVE A STORY FOR YOU
THAT WILL SHAKE THIS TOWN.

41:23.757 --> 41:27.327
IT'S ABOUT JUDGE CRYER.

41:27.327 --> 41:29.062
CAN WE MEET?

41:29.062 --> 41:33.499
♪♪♪♪

41:33.499 --> 41:35.135
GREAT.

41:35.135 --> 41:37.370
<i>NEXT ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:37.370 --> 41:38.739
‐ROSE ‐‐
‐THE REPORTER?

41:38.739 --> 41:40.774
SHE CALLED MY OFFICE,
SAID SHE HAD A FEW QUESTIONS

41:40.774 --> 41:43.376
SHE WOULD LIKE TO ASK ME
ABOUT HOW I FEEL

41:43.376 --> 41:47.380
ABOUT ELECTED OFFICIALS
AND PROSTITUTES.

41:47.380 --> 41:48.549
MAMA ‐‐

41:48.549 --> 41:50.817
[ Voice breaking ]
YOU MORTGAGED MY HOUSE!

41:50.817 --> 41:51.852
HERE'S YOUR MONEY.

41:51.852 --> 41:53.286
PICK IT UP NOW!

41:53.286 --> 41:56.222
I THINK DAVID
IS HAVING AN AFFAIR.

41:56.222 --> 41:58.424
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
GIVE ME THAT.

41:58.424 --> 42:01.367
SNOOPING WILL GET YOU FIRED.

42:01.367 --> 42:03.169
IS THIS CANDACE?

42:03.169 --> 42:05.305
I KNEW THERE WAS SOMETHING
UP WITH THAT GIRL.
